{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0098-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Automerge Investigation",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1773859676415,
  "modified": 1742860800000,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Outcome: "
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "Automerge is not the right approach for Hobson. The impedance mismatch between Automerge's operation-level model and Hobson's snapshot-based API creates permanent complexity (diffing layer, map key ordering, bootstrap chicken-and-egg) that outweighs the benefits. A simpler design based on snapshot history + nested instance promotion was chosen instead. See "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "id": "c0c0c0c0-009b-0000-0000-000000000000",
            "s": "History, Versioning & Sync Design"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "Investigate whether Automerge is the right storage foundation for Hobson's next phase: system-level undo + mobile sync."
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Context"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Two upcoming needs converge on the same problem:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "System-level undo."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Deleting an item, removing an attachment, changing a type are all irreversible. The system needs a way to revert destructive operations."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Mobile sync."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Hobson needs to be accessible on mobile, which requires syncing data between devices with conflict resolution."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Automerge is a CRDT library that potentially solves both: its operation log gives history/undo, and its CRDT foundation enables sync with automatic conflict resolution."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Proposed Architecture"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Automerge lives in the kernel storage layer. The rest of Hobson does not interact with Automerge directly."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Read path"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A.load(bytes) → Automerge doc → convert to plain JS object → return to caller. Callers receive a mutable plain object, never an Automerge proxy. This is functionally necessary because callers mutate the returned object before passing it back to api.set()."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Write path"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Caller passes a plain JS object (as today) → storage layer diffs it against the current Automerge doc → applies minimal A.change() mutations at field level (not character level) → A.save() → bytes to IDB. This preserves the existing api.set(item) interface."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "History and revert"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "History/revert belongs in the kernel storage layer, not as a userland item — item edits must not be able to break the history mechanism. The storage API would expose:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.getHistory(itemId)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — list of changes with timestamps and messages"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.viewAt(itemId, heads)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — read-only plain object at a historical state (uses A.view(), which is cheap)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.revertTo(itemId, heads)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — reverts item to a previous state by diffing and applying reverse patches"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A userland history-view can call these APIs for the UI, but the mechanism itself is protected in the kernel."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Query"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Automerge has no cross-document query mechanism. Hobson already maintains indexes in related-items-lib. The existing query/search pattern (load items, filter in JS) continues to work. A lightweight metadata index could avoid deserialising full items for bulk queries."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Open Questions"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Read conversion performance."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " api.get() returns a plain object clone (JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(doc))). This is sub-millisecond per item, but getAll() on 337+ items needs benchmarking. Alternative: return Automerge proxies directly for reads, clone only when caller needs mutability. Needs prototyping to see what breaks."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Write diffing complexity."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " The storage layer must diff a plain JS object against an Automerge doc to produce fine-grained A.change() mutations. Object/primitive fields are straightforward. Arrays (tags, attachments, Active Text ASTs) need a diffing strategy — element-by-element comparison with fallback to full replacement. Needs prototyping."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Storage overhead."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Automerge stores full operation history. For Hobson's whole-field-value pattern, overhead is estimated at 2-3x raw JSON. Need to measure on real items."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "WASM dependency."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Automerge's core is Rust compiled to WASM. Adds to initial load time and requires async initialisation. Need to measure impact on boot."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Undo for deleted items."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " Reverting a field change is straightforward (diff + reverse patches). But reverting item deletion means the item's Automerge doc must still exist somewhere. May need soft-delete (mark as deleted, keep the doc) rather than actual removal."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Sync architecture."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " What does mobile sync look like? automerge-repo handles document lifecycle and sync adapters. A sync server (or peer-to-peer via WebRTC) is needed. This is a later concern but the storage layer should not preclude it."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Alternatives."
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " PouchDB was considered but its revision system discards old bodies on compaction — designed for sync conflict resolution, not version history. Yjs is another CRDT option but has a different storage model. A custom IDB history store (copy-on-write) is simpler but doesn't help with sync."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Prototype Plan"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Before committing to Automerge, build a minimal prototype to get hard numbers:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Take a representative large item (view with hundreds of lines of code, doc with a big Active Text AST)."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Create an Automerge doc from it. Measure A.from() and A.save() sizes."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Measure JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(doc)) conversion time, singly and in bulk (337x)."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Implement a naive field-level diff (old doc vs new plain object). Measure diffing + A.change() time."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Test Active Text AST mutations: insert block, change block type, edit text. Verify Automerge handles the nested structure correctly."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Measure A.getHistory(), A.view(), and A.diff() on a doc with ~50 changes."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "If the prototype shows acceptable performance, proceed with integrating Automerge into the kernel storage layer. If not, evaluate whether proxy-based reads (skipping conversion) or a simpler custom approach is needed."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":hr"
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Benchmark Results (2026-03-19)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Automerge 3.2.4, Firefox, standalone HTML harness (perf/automerge-bench.html). Write/history numbers from spatial-canvas-view (52.5KB, largest item). A.load() scaling tested across five items from 1.3KB to 52.5KB."
        }
      ],
